rComments: Loved this prof honestly. His slides are always super organized and easy to understand. His exams are straight to the point. He explains everything very well and records all of the lectures. Homework every week but it's quick and easy practice. Overall very solid teacher, everything is always clear on what you have to do.
Best prof for stats hands down!

I enjoyed this class very much! Stats have never really been my strongest but with professor Rousseau, I was able to quickly build a strong foundation and I am hoping to have him for other classes. I recommend taking his classes as his lectures are very helpful and he gives lots of feedback if you reach out to him. Lots of room for improvement!

Prof. Rousseau was a great professor who really cared. Statistics is not my strong suit but he gave us opportunities to succeed. He is someone who is approachable and down-to-earth, but also professional and knowledgeable.

I enjoyed this class as the professor was very nice and wanted the best for the students. I was able to improve quite a bit over the semester as professor Rousseau gave lots of opportunities to improve and the possibility of dropping the lowest quiz grade which really helped my grade. I would recommend taking stats courses with him!

This class was definitely informative with Dr. Rousseau. He is always giving Opportunities to do better on future exams/quizzes and he is very lenient with grades. I would advise going to all the lectures and reaching out to him and the TA's when running into problems. Overall I would say this class is easy if you study and attend the lectures!

Professor Rousseau is an amazing lecturer! He is very lenient with grades and he is always making sure students are on the right track. He is always following up with you if you run into problems. The lectures are very organized and it's important to attend them all. He is very accessible outside of class whether it's over email or an office hour.
His lectures are straight forward and to the point. He is pretty lenient with his grading which is nice.
Overall great. He gives so many options to re weight assessments to get the best grade possible he teaches on a practical level (stuff you would actually need to know how to do) not just theory.

He's a nice prof but not the best at actually explaining the content. Really lenient with grading though (drops lowest quiz mark, reweighting, curving) so you can still manage to do pretty decent. Quizzes/midterms weren't too difficult but you kind of had to teach yourself all of it
not bad. I didn't like him at first, but the class grew on me, and I finished with an A+, so I can't complain

The class averages were high (80+) for the midterms so obviously, the class wasn't that hard. The final average was a bit harder lower than the midterms but honestly, if you studied at all it wasn't bad. Overall good professor. He even dropped the lowest quiz score and gave us a lot of options to reweight the quizzes to the final.

Whoa did not expect the reviews to be so harsh. He is not good on the spot and practice questions would have helped but his suggestion to make a spreadsheet with the assumptions was a lifesaver. The key is to review the slides before class to ask questions and understand the theory behind the examples. He reweighs the quizzes and drops the lowest.

To do well, you have to teach yourself and try to connect the dots on your own, since there are no practice problems. It wasn't a horrible class, but it was unnecessarily stressful. The material itself is not difficult but I think the prof could have taught better.

I don't think I have ever had such a terrible professor. He takes too long to respond to emails and trust me when I say I did not learn anything at all. He does not give practice questions and he somehow decides it is better to go over material after the exam is over instead of teaching it before. Save yourself time and do your research on profs.

AVOID THIS PROFESSOR! He did not teach a single thing all semester long. He gives you barely any time to finish quizzes and so questions are left blank. He spends an hour and half weekly talking nonsense and then tests you on material he never mentioned or practiced during class. Save yourself time, this guy does not know what he is doing.

worst prof i have had in the 3 years of university, i cannot describe how horrible he is, avoid at all cost for the sake of your mental wellbeing, he is arrogant for no reason and clearly stats is not his forte. He should not be teaching any math class
He assumes that everyone knows everything already, and DOESN'T GIVE US ANY PRACTICE since he "doesn't have enough time to make questions" and there's no textbook so good luck
An entire mess of a prof that cant teach stats to save his life, honestly one of the worst classes i've taken so far

DO NOT TAKE HSS2382 WITH THIS PROF. There is barely any examples in class slides and he gives no homework or resources to practice. When asked to give homework he said that he "did not have time". It's really hard to understand concepts without examples or practice of application of things we are learning until the tests or quizzes.
I didn't like him as a prof. He seems nice but he doesn't give you any practice questions so you are on your own. Doesn't reply to emails.

This is the second time I've had this prof and I liked him even better this time around. He organized the class in a way that makes it easy to get a good grade. There is 10 weekly group assignments but he only counts the 8 best marks, a participation mark, a midterm and a final.

Gives so many opportunities to get an A! Seriously, there is no reason you can't get an amazing grade in this class if you just complete all the extra little tasks which are not long. Also, I thought I would hate stats and ended up looking forward to his lectures and learning things that were really useful. Philippe is also extremely caring. 10/10.

If you're taking stats and you struggle with math, TAKE THIS PROF. He doesn't make you memorize any equations. The class is just learning how to use which test (ex. t test, mann whitney, chi square, ANOVA) and when to use them. The TA was really helpful too in the labs because he gave us resources to practice on which test was which. Recommend!

Rousseau is great prof. You can tell he is really passionate about what he teaches and he really takes the time to teach the material. His exam was short answers so you had to know your stuff to do well, but I found it to be very fair. Also, his powerpoint are pretty complete so you don't really have to take a lot of notes in class.
A very kind and approachable person that cares about each student individually. Although, it seemed he did not have much experience teaching this course, he is a very knowledgeable professor.

An exceptional professor. I had taken this course in a different section before and could not understand it and ended up failing. Rousseau takes time to make sure no student is left behind in the course material. I found a new understanding and appreciation for statistics. He also is very understanding and easy to talk to. I highly recommend him.

He is such a great guy and genuinely cares about his class, my only complaint is that he doesn't explain content fully(half expecting you to know already) and goes by very quickly (so you can't take notes in class) and within a statistics class it can get confusing as it adds up. Overall, an okay class but not my type of learning is all

One of the best profs I've had so far in Communication. He cares about his students, wants to help you do well and really understand the material. I thought I would hate this course but I really enjoyed it. I'd take any of his classes again!

This prof really made quantitative easy for us! He was super friendly and knew a lot of students names, it really made for a nice atmosphere! His slides explain everything, and the labs while they can be tricky they pan out! My best advice is study hard, review the lab notes before the lab, and ask questions in labs!

He seems like a great guy, really nice and caring. But, I don't like him as a communication prof. The course was basically math. COMMUNICATION students don't do math! The mid term was horrid so if you suck at math good luck. The labs were annoying, then he changed the approach. The proposal and final got more confusing the more he tried to help.

Really made quantitative analysis and math stuff easy to understand for communications students. The labs were super helpful for SPSS. Midterm and final papers easy to score well on if you do it properly/follow guidelines - midterm exam straightforward and graded very fairly. Also super responsive over email/outside of class.
Dr. Rousseau is a great prof, he is always there for students. Very knowledgeable in Biomechanics.  Also has very clear expectations for exams, class average was a high 70.
Great prof! He made biomechanics enjoyable and always ensured that students understood the material.
Dr. Rousseau is one of the best teachers I've ever had! Very helpful, inspirational, and knows how to make his lectures interesting.  I would definitely recommend his class!

Dr. Rousseau is a professor who presents his material effectively, including problem solving in class and extra problems for home practice. He takes the time to learn students' names and really does his best to get an interactive lecture going. On top of that, he always looks on point when he lectures. One of my all-time favourite teachers.

He is an excellent professor who really cares about his students. He takes the time to explain basic concepts so more complex ones are easy to understand. Class is very helpful to explain theory based questions and he posts full solutions to all practice problems.  He always clarifies any extra questions. Would definitely recommend his class!

Go to the classes, he is very elaborate in his explanation, and this is the only time when you can get the answer to his written answer style questions in lectures (his slides don't include the answers). Overall he is an incredible Prof, if you have the chance to take his class do it! He really cares about his students and makes classes relatable.

He is very supportive and cares about the success of his students. He is more than happy to offer help outside of class and is passionate about what he teaches. His slideshows are great and show the math step-by-step without skipping stuff. Amazing prof!
Vraiment facile comme matière il adore ce qu'il enseigne et le transmet bien
Vraiment intéressant. Connait très bien sa matière et la transmet très bien. Répond aux questions de façon claire et précise.

He taught the biomechanics section of the course, and was fantastic. He makes things really clear, and in the labs he really tries to make sure everyone understands. He's one of those profs whose passion shines through a bit when he's telling you what he thinks is cool. Also, suuuper hot. I missed a couple classes and I regretted it! Exam was fair.
